# bayanihan — local environment configuration (example)
#
# Copy to .env and edit as needed. `.env` is gitignored; this `.env.example` is
# committed as documentation. Every script works with the defaults below WITHOUT a
# .env when the repo layout is standard — these are optional overrides only.

# Root of the large, gitignored data that the scripts/ runners read and write
# (recovered EDP source tables, per-building portfolio detail, the .mat anchors).
# Defaults to <repo>/sandbox. Override only if you keep that data outside the repo.
# BAYANIHAN_DATA_DIR=/absolute/path/to/your/data
